History Guy: Son of Russian czar visited Topeka

A member of Russian royalty came to Topeka in 1872. This weeks History Guy video at CJOnline focuses on that visit by Grand Duke Alexis, the son of Russian Czar Alexander II and younger brother of Czar Alexander III. Alexander II was still czar when the 21-year-old Alexis traveled in 1871 to Washington, D.C., where he was received by President Ulysses S. Grant. Topeka High girls No. 1 in KBCA poll

Topeka Highs girls will begin the 2020-21 basketball season exactly where most people figured they would end last season. No. 1. The Trojans posted a 23-0 mark in 2019-20 but saw their bid for an undefeated state title end prematurely when the state tournaments were canceled after the semifinals for COVID-19 concerns. In rolling to the semifinals, High had just two games all season decided by less than 10 points.
